r in Group B as compared to Group C. Tibial trabecular bone volume fraction in female was greater in Group C as compared to the other groups. Trabecular thickness in femaletibiawas also greater in Group C compared to other two groups; while, trabecular thickness of female radius was higher in Group C compared to Group A. Conclusions: Skeletal microarchitecture is altered in T1D subjects with and without celiac disease. This may explain higher skeletal fragility in this subgroup of patients.},
 author = {Soham Mukherjee, S. Bhadada, R. Pal, V. Dhiman, Anmol Verma, A. Kaur},
 title = {Abstract 71: Assessment of skeletal microarchitecture by high resolution peripheral quantitative computed tomography (HR-pQCT) in patients with type 1 diabetes},
